Night waneth fast, the morning star Saddens with light the glimm’ring sea,

Whose weves shall soon to realms afar Waft me from hope, from love, and thee.

Coldly the beem from yonder sky

Looks o'er the waves that onwar'd stray3 But eolder still the stranger’s eye

To him whose home is far away.

Oh, not at hour so chill end bleak

Let thoughts of me come 0’er thy breast3 But of the lost one think and speak When summer suns sink calm to rest.
